CONFIRMED genuine skip (#3) — needs the removed canterp.so Python interpreter plugin.

The test runs `rs274 -p ${LIBDIR}/linuxcnc/canterp.so -g canon`: it loads canterp
(the "canonical interpreter" written in Python) as an alternate interpreter plugin
via an ABSOLUTE path. canterp.so is a Python C-extension and is not built once the
embedded Python interpreter is removed, so there is no plugin to load — and the
whole `-p <python-plugin>` alternate-interpreter mechanism has no non-Python plugin
to exercise. plug/{absolute,filename,relative} only differ in how the (missing)
plugin path is resolved. Genuine removal, nothing to re-express.
